Company SRMG
Date 4/29/2021 10:30:00 PM
Calendar Event Type General Assembly
Event Result -
Venue -
Details

Shareholders will vote to amend article (2) of the company’s articles of association, to change the firm’s name to Saudi Research and Media Group. Shareholders will also vote to elect members of the board of directors for the next three-year term, starting May 21, 2021. They will also vote on the formation of the audit committee, and determine its duties, work regulations and remuneration of its members for the upcoming term.

Company Overview

Our Arabic dailies were the first to offer the world a perspective rooted in and informed by our region. We launched Saudi Arabia’s first ever English newspaper, we were the first to launch a pan-Arab women’s weekly, and the first in the region to print newspapers in colour. landscape. From in-the-moment content to news channels, apps and digital platforms, we are accelerating towards the future. We’re harnessing the best human talent, data, insights, and technology to build smarter, more meaningful ways to connect with a mass audience

Business

The company is the publisher of Al-Sharq Al-Awsat newspaper among other publications. It also operates in the printing, advertising and publicity sectors.

05/04/2020

SRMG subsidiary inks agreement to buy 51% of Thmanyah Publishing for SAR 33.3 mln

SRMG subsidiary inks agreement to buy 51% of Thmanyah Publishing for SAR 33.3 mln

05/04/2020

Agreement signing

Saudi Research and Media Group’s (SRMG) subsidiary, Arab Media Co., signed, on July 13, an interest purchase agreement with Abdulrahman Ali Abumalih, Aseel Salah Baabdullah and Meem Company for Research and Studies, to acquire 51% of stake in Thmanyah Company for Publishing and Distribution for SAR 33.31 million, the company said in a bourse filing.

The transaction amount includes the purchase price and capital injection in Thmanyah Company. It will be funded from the SRMG’s resources and cash flows.

Thmanyah Company for Publishing and Distribution is a leading digital media company in Saudi Arabia and is involved in producing and distributing Arabic podcasts and documentaries on social media platforms.

However, the transaction is subject to the completion of several preconditions, including obtaining required regulatory approvals from the Ministry of Commerce to amend the articles of association of Thmanyah Company for Publishing and Distribution to introduce the Arab Media Co. as a new partner. Besides, approval of the General Authority for Competition and any other regulatory approvals will be required.

The agreement includes the customary warranties and representations provided by sellers in similar transactions, the statement said.

There is no direct impact on the SRMG’s obligations. The financial impact of this transaction is expected to reflect from Q4 2021.

SRMG’s acquisition of Thmanyah is part of the group’s new multi-platform approach and commitment to delivering original, unique and exclusive content to consumers through new digital and social platforms.

The company said that completing the transaction or any other material developments will be announced in due course.

There are no related parties, the statement noted.

Details

Shareholders will vote to amend article (2) of the company’s articles of association, to change the firm’s name to Saudi Research and Media Group. Shareholders will also vote to elect members of the board of directors for the next three-year term, starting May 21, 2021. They will also vote on the formation of the audit committee, and determine its duties, work regulations and remuneration of its members for the upcoming term.
